  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The goal of the proposed research is to examine the neural correlates of depressive symptom
      reduction in individuals with major depressive disorder using functional magnetic resonance
      imaging (fMRI), and to compare results to those obtained from a nondepressed control group.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
