  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  For group 1: Diagnosis of current depression and no other current Axis I psychiatric
             disorder

          -  For group 1: Hamilton Depression Rating Scale score of 15 or greater

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  A history of serious head injury or neurological disease or psychosis

          -  Current use of psychoactive medications

          -  Factors that could affect MRI safety including current or planned pregnancy

          -  For group 2: current Axis I psychiatric disorder, as assessed by structured clinical
             interview
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
